# Project Map — Read First

Before making any changes, read `PROJECT_MAP.md` in the project root.

It contains:
- What this project is and how it works
- Full file structure with the purpose of every file
- The global `window.Nextscope` namespace and which module owns what
- Data flow from file/serial input to the Plotly chart
- Conventions you must follow (no bundler, IIFE pattern, script load order, SweetAlert2, localStorage keys, CSS variables, `sw.js` cache version)
- Hardware context (NextPower telemetry column names)

Do not skip this step. The project has non-obvious conventions (no ES modules, shared global namespace, specific script load order) that will cause bugs if ignored.

## Updating the Map
After any major change (new file, new struct, refactor, new convention),
update PROJECT_MAP.md before closing the task.
